block content
    div.
        <p><strong>»</strong> The complexity of the today’s projects mandates efficient planning, cost management, and time
            management.<br>
            Involvement of many partners in construction contracts also requires the thorough and professional analysis and
            management of project’s document.</p>
        <p><strong>»</strong> As a project manager, <strong>ECB</strong> assigns a team of highly qualified professionals
            who will take total ownership of the project.<br>
            This team will become the pillar of the project, The team will be the point of coordination and contact between
            the client and all projects’ stakeholders during all phases of the project.</p>
        <p><strong>»</strong> Our experienced project management staff works actively to ensure the project’s success in
            coherence with the client’s needs and project specification.<br>
            Through the proper control and management of the project’s different phases, we ensure that the projects are
            completed on schedule, within budget, and with the desired quality.</p>
        <p><strong>» ECB</strong> provides <strong>Project Management Services</strong> in full spectrum or in individual
            tasks for the following scopes:</p>
        <p>★ Design Management.<br>
            ★ Tendering &amp; Procurement.<br>
            ★ Contract Administration.<br>
            ★ Construction Management.<br>
            ★ Scheduling and Time Management.<br>
            ★ Cost Management &amp; Budgeting.<br>
            ★ Claims Management.</p>
        <p>&nbsp;</p>
        <p><strong>★ DESIGN MANAGEMENT</strong></p>
        <p>Design management, through a dedicated design manager working with the project manager on behalf of the owner,
            primarily seeks to establish project management practices that are focused on enhancing the design process
            across the entire design team.<br>
            The successful implementation of owner focused design management throughout the entire project lifecycle can
            represent the difference between the success and failure of the project.</p>
        <p><strong>★ TENDERING &amp; PROCUREMENT</strong></p>
        <p>An effective procurement management and tender process provides a positive evaluation approach that leads not
            only to the appointment of appropriate consultant, contractor and suppliers but to ensure that the ongoing
            relationship is mutually beneficial.<br>
            A wholly balanced and highly efficient tender management process improves the quality of the project while
            reducing costs and managing risks.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>
        <p><strong>★ CONTRACT MANAGEMENT</strong></p>
        <p>Since the poor administration of construction contract agreement could jeopardize the overall success of the
            project, we manage and administer contracts with the highest level of professionalism and with the help of our
            high-caliber contract expertise.</p>
        <p><strong>★ CONSTRUCTION MANAGEMENT</strong></p>
        <p>ECB’s treats the design and construction phases as integrated stages; therefore, it is imperative that our CM
            professionals are involved in the project since the earliest stages of design.<br>
            The involvement of the CM in the early phases of the project’s design has proven to be efficient and effective,
            Our CM personnel can offer valuable advice during the design stages that will help avoid any costly change order
            after the construction contract is awarded.</p>
        <p><strong>★ TIME MANAGEMENT</strong></p>
        <p>We believe that a well-planned job is a half-done job. Therefore, our scheduling and planning professional work
            on applying a set of strategies and planning techniques to ensure timely completion of all project’s phases and
            mile stones. Our planning &amp; scheduling consultants understand our client’s ideas and objectives and
            transform them to program and mile stones. Then they control the program throughout the project’s execution by
            ensuring that the contractor is in full coherence with the project’s predefined time schedule and plan.</p>
        <p><strong>★ COST MANAGEMENT</strong></p>
        <p>Cost management is one of the most important aspects in a successful project, The main objective of our cost
            management division is to maintain and control project’s cost within the prescribed projects’ budget.</p>
        <p><strong>★ CLAIMS MANAGEMENT</strong></p>
        <p>Claims and disputes are inevitable in the construction industry.<br>
            Our job is to early identify those claims and try to advice on any necessary avoidance plan.<br>
            Our claims management &amp; resolution professional will represent the owner in any claims or disputes that
            might arise during the project.</p>